meta.name: Emmerdale
meta.description: Emmerdale is a British soap focusing on the lives of several families and locals living around an estate, a farm and the nearby village in the Yorkshire Dales. It is the second longest British soap in television history since airing its first episode on ITV in 1972, as 'Emmerdale Farm', the show was renamed in 1989.

videos.title: Monday 16th October 1972
videos.overview: On the day of Jacob's funeral, the Sugden family are shocked to discover that Emmerdale Farm has been left to the recently returned Jack, causing fury amongst Jacob's other children, Peggy and Joe

videos.title: Tuesday 17th October 1972
videos.overview: Matt confronts Peggy over his suspicions about her, and she reveals she is in fact pregnant. The revelation pushes the pair to decide to get their own place.

videos.title: Monday 23rd October 1972
videos.overview: Annie pushes Jack to make decisions regarding the farm. Meanwhile, Joe takes Marian on a fishing trip, bringing the two closer together

videos.title: Monday 30th October 1972
videos.overview: Joe finds out from Amos that Jack was seen coming out of the barn with Marian. He goes to the Wilks farm to find Jack is there. Since Marian broke Matt's fishing rod that Peggy gave him, Joe borrows money from 3 people to fix it. When Annie finds out, she confronts Joe. Peggy is angry that Matt is doing all the work while Jack and Joe are chasing Marian.

videos.title: Tuesday 12th November 1985
videos.overview: On the day of the Beckindale Harvest Festival, the Sugdens remember Sam, whilst Amos is determined to win. Meanwhile, Derek threatens Harry with Sgt. MacArthur sniffing around...

videos.title: Tuesday 16th December 1986
videos.overview: Preparations getting underway for Alan's N.Y. Estates gathering. Seth (Stan Richards) expects the party to be boring and secretly plans to spice it up. Annie (Sheila Mercier) leaves a goose for Sandie (Jane Hutcheson) and Phil (Peter Alexander). He thanks her for inviting them both to the farm for Christmas. Jock (Drew Dawson) and Bill (Johnny Caesar) chuckle as Seth makes a phone call in The Woolpack. Dolly (Jean Rogers) takes Sam (Benjamin Whitehead) for a walk through the woods as the youth (Ross Kemp) continues to watch her. Preparations for the nativity play gets underway at St. Mary's Church and Jack (Clive Hornby) helps out. Jack comments to Donald (Hugh Manning) that it's the first time he's been in the church since Pat's funeral. The N.Y. Estates gathering gets underway at Home Farm and Alan (Richard Thorp) is pleased as everyone appears to be enjoying themselves. He's embarrassed, however, when a stripper girl (Rebecca Sowden) dressed up as Santa arrives and kisses him. Annie, Henry (Arthur Pentelow), Amos (Ronald Magill) and Donald look on mortified as Seth, Jock and Bill chortle in the background.

videos.title: Wednesday 12th April 1989
videos.overview: Kate is at the church, with no sign of Joe but ex-husband David watching and waiting - and another unexpected guest finds himself with a key role. Nick, meanwhile, discovers why Clare isn't keen to marry him.

videos.title: Tuesday 28th December 1993
videos.overview: It's Christmas Day in Beckindale - there's a festive gathering for the Sugdens and a lonely day for Kim and Seth, and the new arrivals play host to an uninvited guest.

videos.title: Thursday 30th December 1993
videos.overview: Jack and Joe fuss over Annie and Leonard. Zoe arrives home and invites Frank to the Woolpack. A disaster engulfs the village and things will never be the same again.

videos.title: Tuesday 4th January 1994
videos.overview: Nick is blinded and wanders around looking for Archie. Frank surveys the devastation in the village. Survivors begin to congregate at the Woolpack.

videos.title: Wednesday 5th January 1994
videos.overview: Lynn's house is still on fire. Alan puts together a missing persons list. Shirley arranges a base for the emergency services to work from. The villagers repair the bridge.

videos.title: Thursday 6th January 1994
videos.overview: Frank tells Chris he is going to be helicoptered out of the village. Eric still can't find Elizabeth. There's some grave news for the Sugden family.

videos.title: Tuesday 19th January 1999
videos.overview: Kim heads to Home Farm for a final confrontation with Chris to get her money back and things take a violent turn. Graham storms out after an argument with Rachel.

videos.title: Thursday 2nd December 1999
videos.overview: Kelly is in a state and confides in Mandy that perhaps Chris was right - she'll never be happy with Roy. Zoe offers Terry extra money to look after Chris and keep him company. Paddy's cousin Jason turns up out of the blue saying he's fallen out with his parents after revealing he's gay. Tricia takes an immediate shine to him at the Woolpack and Diane overhears Gavin say to her that she used to look at him like that. As she leaves to go home Diane warns Gavin she'll not stand to see her Bernice hurt again. And Mandy gets a call to say her dad's been taken ill again. She rushes off telling Paddy she'll be back the following day.

videos.title: Friday 20th December 2002
videos.overview: Louise makes plans to leave the village. Sam's investigations unearth a fortune in a Chilean bank. Ollie and Danny's living arrangements cause strife for Len.

videos.title: November 12, 2007
videos.overview: Paul is disgruntled when Rodney talks to him yet again about his commitment to Jonny, but he doesn't admit his secret doubts. When Jonny tells Paul that he'll be out for the night Paul heads to the pub to drown his sorrows.

videos.title: November 13, 2007
videos.overview: Paul has spent the night at his mum's and he heads over to see Jonny to smooth things over. But Jonny is devastated by Paul's betrayal and refuses to forgive him.

videos.title: November 14, 2007
videos.overview: Eli is wild with jealousy when he learns that Debbie's got a new bloke and Chas realises that he's smitten with his cousin. Eli goes to the garage to see Debbie and questions her about Sean, but she warns him off. Eli is even more miserable when Debbie meets Sean in the pub in a knockout dress and he glumly watches them leave for a meal in Hotten.

videos.title: November 15, 2007
videos.overview: Eli is downbeat about Debbie's new relationship but on his bin run, he spots Sean outside a house with what appears to be his wife and children!

videos.title: November 16, 2007
videos.overview: Jo is troubled by her deteriorating relationship with Andy and Jack picks up on the tension. Jack tells Jo that Andy loves her and he will need her more than ever if he gets sent down.

videos.title: December 2, 2007
videos.overview: Jasmine and Miles go to the hospital where Donald is on a life support machine and they hide when they see Nicola. The pair begin to bond over Nicola's catalogue of evil deeds and Jasmine's feelings for Miles begin to grow.

videos.title: December 3, 2007
videos.overview: Miles falls off the wagon when Nicola finds him and brings up his mother. Victoria continues to be rude to Diane, and Emily tries to make amends with Lisa and Debbie.

videos.title: December 4, 2007
videos.overview: Jasmine's article about Nicola makes the front page, leaving Rodney shocked about her behaviour. Jack has a heart-to-heart with Victoria about Diane and Paul and Jonny grow closer.

videos.title: December 5, 2007
videos.overview: Nicola seduces David and Jasmine wonders if he was faithful when they were together. Chas and Lexi sell their bionic bears and Katie and Gray grow closer.

videos.title: December 6, 2007
videos.overview: Grayson is horrified when he learns that Donna and Ross came across Rosemary's car abandoned in the bushes close to one of the Kings' properties, Manor Farm.

videos.title: December 31, 2007
videos.overview: It's New Year's Eve and after discovering that Rosmary is to be buried next to their father, Matt storms into the Woolpack on the stroke of midnight and punches Grayson in the face. Lexi and Chas make a vow to stay single in 2008.

videos.title: January 1, 2008
videos.overview: Matthew, determined to stop Rosemary being buried next to Tom gets Carl & Jimmy to help him fill in the grave but is taken away by police, He returns later on with a dustbin lorry. Perdy tells Grayson that she wants a divorce.

videos.title: Thurs 1st January 2009
videos.overview: Donna thinks Ross might become a suspect for the police. Marlon stumbles across the couple. Val doesn't like Daz and Victoria being together.

videos.title: Fri 2nd January 2009
videos.overview: Marlon tells the police about Shane's blackmailing. Val tells Daz to stay away from Victoria. Lily and Edna try to make up.

videos.title: Mon 5th January 2009
videos.overview: When Ross returns to the village and attacks Marlon, he makes a shocking discovery. Jimmy struggles with organizing the funeral.

videos.title: Monday 9th February
videos.overview: Diane returns to the village with Annie for Jack's funeral. Victoria seeks reassurances from Annie that Jack hadn't forgotten about her and gets some peace of mind when Annie begins reminiscing. Alan agrees to help organise the service. Annie is alarmed to hear that Andy is having doubts about whether to attend, but Daz says he'll make sure that he's there.

videos.title: Tuesday 10th February
videos.overview: Victoria prepares herself for Jack's funeral and tells an upset Daz that she's planning to move to Spain with Annie. Daz begs Victoria to change her mind and almost admits his feelings for her, but stops himself just in time as the hearse arrives to take them to the funeral. Meanwhile, Robert is watching from a distance.

videos.title: Tuesday 10th February
videos.overview: Victoria prepares herself for Jack's funeral and tells an upset Daz that she's planning to move to Spain with Annie. videos.title: Friday 1st January

videos.title: Monday 3rd January
videos.overview: Eric is avoiding Val and she is avoiding him. Amy tells David about Michael's accusations. David tries to speak to Eric but he walks away. Adam breaks up with Scarlett, she is devastated. Will is playing games with Belle, he keeps getting calls on his mobile and eventually throws it on the floor, breaking it. He confides in Belle that Nathan keeps calling him. Ella goes to Jai for advice on how to win Declan back. Eric tells Val about what happened with Elizabeth and how he couldn't let her keep implicating him.

videos.title: Thurs 23 Oct 2014 Pt1
videos.overview: James worries. Bernice is alarmed. Ross feels guilty as Dan wishes he never knew what Kerry did.

videos.title: Thurs 23 Oct 2014 Pt2
videos.overview: Robert explains to Chrissie who 'Andrew' and 'Katherine' really are. Megan rejects Jai's offer of a loan when he leads her to believe it's money that he would have been using to find Archie.
